# SelyoPass — Cursor rules

Read AGENTS.md at the project root for the full agent guide (overview, architecture, build/test,
conventions, and /docs references). Ground every change in idea.md + /docs, not memory.

Load-bearing rules to never break:
- Never put document bytes or PII on-chain — only the document hash (BR-002, non-custodial).
- Never present a "verified / trust-this-business" compliance stamp; SelyoPass is a data courier,
  and compliance liability stays with the relying institution (BR-003, BSP Circular 1170).
- Never handle the user's private key — signing is Freighter's job; never hardcode an issuer key.
- Testnet only, Freighter only, Philippines only for the MVP (idea.md §10).
- Every code change ties to an F-### that has a test in docs/11-qa-test-plan.md.

For scoped, path-specific rules, see ./.cursor/rules/*.mdc (none generated for this MVP).
